# ZizkaDB Testing Conventions

## Run tests
```bash
# Unit only (no stack)
pytest core/tests/ -m "not integration" -v

# Integration (stack on :8000)
pytest core/tests/ -m integration -v

# Skip OpenAI-dependent tests
pytest core/tests/ -m "integration and not requires_openai" -v

# Pre-push
bash scripts/verify-release.sh

# Full workflow
bash scripts/test-e2e-workflow.sh
```

## Pytest markers (`core/pytest.ini`)
- `integration` — requires Docker stack
- `requires_openai` — needs `OPENAI_API_KEY`
- `security` — auth/isolation tests
- `slow` — load tests

## When adding API behavior
1. Find scenario in `.cursor/skills/zizkadb-testing/scenario-catalog.md`
2. Add test in `core/tests/test_integration_*.py`
3. Use fixtures from `core/tests/conftest.py` (`dev_headers`, `jwt_headers`, `api_base`)
4. Never skip tenant isolation (B9) or agent scope (B6/B7) for new routes

## P0 regressions (must always pass)
- B6/B7 agent-scoped key enforcement
- B9 cross-tenant isolation
- C1 log event, C2 causal why chain
- E1 search 400 without embedding key
- E11 GDPR forget removes events

## Test file layout
- `test_smoke.py` — unit + legacy integration
- `test_integration_auth.py` — auth matrix
- `test_integration_events.py` — log, query, why, at
- `test_integration_search.py` — search, context, forget

## SDK changes
- Python unit tests in `core/tests/` or `sdk/python/tests/`
- Manual or future automated TS parity check

## Do not
- Commit secrets in test fixtures
- Rely on smoke-test.sh alone for new features
- Skip integration tests for cross-service paths (PG + Qdrant)
